page.title: 12LAND COVER
page.content: The following percentages indicate uses of land: {74.8%}- arable farmland (crops grown: wheat, barley, peas, potatoes, sugar-beet and old seed rape). {9.6%}- residential land {5.5%}- deciduous woodland {5.25%}- pasture/grassland {1.3%}- community services {1.2%}- urban space {0.75%}- wasteland {0.6%}- market gardening {0.4%}- industrial land {0.3%}- coniferous woodland {0.3%}- lakes/reservoirs {RELIEF { }The south of the are is flat land with the maximum height at 27 metres. Further north the land appears to be slightly hilly and the height drops to a minimum of 10 metres.
